adverse effect and its mechanism for chemotherapy agents?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Cisplatin causes peripheral neuropathy through sodium channel blockade","Vinca alkaloids cause nephrotoxicity through direct tubular damage","Bleomycin causes cardiomyopathy through calcium channel disruption","Methotrexate causes ototoxicity through cochlear inflammation","Anthracyclines cause cardiotoxicity through free radical generation"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct association is that \u003Cstrong\u003Eanthracyclines cause cardiotoxicity through free radical generation\u003C/strong\u003E. Anthracyclines like doxorubicin generate reactive oxygen species which are thought to be the major contributor to their cardiotoxic effects. This toxicity is cumulative and dose-dependent.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect associations can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECisplatin causes peripheral neuropathy through sodium channel blockade\u003C/strong\u003E: cisplatin causes peripheral neuropathy via accumulation of platinum adducts in dorsal root ganglia, which causes neurotoxicity via multiple mechanisms.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EVinca alkaloids cause nephrotoxicity through direct tubular damage\u003C/strong\u003E: the most common side effect of vinca alkaloids is neurotoxicity not nephrotoxicity. Vinca alkaloids act on microtubules within the cell - they do not act on renal tubules.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBleomycin causes cardiomyopathy through calcium channel disruption\u003C/strong\u003E: bleomycin\u0027s primary toxicity is pulmonary fibrosis, primarily through oxidative damage to lung tissue.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMethotrexate causes ototoxicity through cochlear inflammation\u003C/strong\u003E: methotrexate typically causes bone marrow suppression and mucositis through its antifolate effects, and is not associated with significant ototoxicity.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUnderstanding the mechanisms of chemotherapy-induced toxicity is crucial for monitoring patients and implementing appropriate preventive strategies.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Vinca alkaloids cause peripheral neuropathy by disrupting microtubule formation in neurons.","Anthracyclines can cause cardiotoxicity through free radical generation and DNA damage.","Bleomycin can cause pulmonary fibrosis mainly through oxidate damage to lung tissue."],"references":["Therapeutic Guidelines. Melbourne: Therapeutic Guidelines Limited. Available from: https://www.tg.org.au","Ritter J, Flower RJ (Rod J), Henderson G (Graeme), et al.\u00a0Rang and Dale\u2019s Pharmacology. Tenth edition. Elsevier; 2024.","Australian Medicines Handbook\u00a0(online). Adelaide: Australian Medicines Handbook Pty Ltd. Available from:\u00a0https://amhonline.amh.net.au/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"94977"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16784"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"94977","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/94977"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-09-08T16:25:15+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-08T16:25:15+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9475"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"112945"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"ht